node.text:
We are thrilled to bring you Any Oregon Sunday, a film that explores the motorcycle adventures of three Oregon women.

This documentary is a snapshot of the diverse community of womxn riders in Oregon. Tiffany Lindquist rides across the state on her Triumph Bonneville meeting Kylee Sweeten, a champion trials bike rider in the Oregon High Desert; Ashley Volner, a versatile dune and moto racer out at the Dunes; and Jada Noriyuki, a dirt bike rider at Brown’s Camp in the Tillamook Forest. Although each rider’s background and story is different, they all do it for the love of the sport and desire to immerse themselves in the beauty of Oregon.

This film was funded in partnership with @oregonfilm 

Production credits: Kanani Koster (director, editor) Janie Faison (animation director, producer) tiffany Lindquist (producer, rider) Jasmine Karcey (director of photography)

See the link in the bio for more details and follow @any_oregon_sunday for how to watch the full film.

node.text: Reconectate con la naturaleza y descubre una de las 7 maravillas de Oregon — las Painted Hills. Ubicadas en el condado de Wheeler, Painted Hills es una serie de colinas de arcilla con tonos rojizas y doradas únicas a Eastern Oregon. Mientras visitas las colinas asegúrate de sólo caminar en las áreas marcadas y permitidas así estarás contribuyendo a preservas este lugar rocoso.

node.text: Camas root has long nourished the people of the Pacific Northwest, serving a pivotal role in the diet and trade of Indigenous communities for at least 10,000 years. And it continues to be a staple for many Tribal families in Oregon today. Learn more at the link in bio.

node.text:
Analise Cleopatra had never ridden a mountain bike before. She had never gone camping, either, and she suffers from long-term anxiety. Yet in 2019, she embarked on a major adventure to push herself out of her comfort zone: She went bikepacking. 
With fellow beginner Dejuanae Toliver and professional mountain biker Brooklyn Bell, she rode 132 miles in a soul-searching expedition through the Willamette Valley and Central Oregon. Here is their story.

This is an #OregonMade production with @rei and @oregonfilm featuring the work of @cleeeopatra, @badgal_brooky, @day_toliver, @alynicklas and @alisageiser. #PedalThrough

In honor of National Lighthouse Day tomorrow, here's your reminder that a trip down Highway 101 isn’t complete without stopping to view its historic lighthouses. 

These beacons of hope are visible links to the past—towering monuments to Oregon’s maritime heritage and to the hardworking people that kept them lit. Although unoccupied since the arrival of modern technology, these classic structures stand as a testament to the history of Oregon’s rugged coast. 

Check out the link for a road trip to all of Oregon's lighthouses.
